<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-112-594  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 112 594.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Jan 15 1990 v4 n2 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cheney unveils DOD reorganization. (Department of Defense, DefenseSecretary Dick Cheney)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>In keeping with the defense budget cuts, Defense Secretary DickCheney announces an information management restructuring thatinvolves the consolidation of major Army, Navy and Air Forceadministrative systems throughout DOD.andP;  The reorganization isaimed at rehabilitating the department's acquisition system andstreamlining DOD management.andP;  Cheney expects the DOD to save $2.3billion in fiscal 1991 and $39 billion from fiscal 1991 throughfiscal 1995.andP;  The changes include the elimination of thousands ofcivilian and military personnel, possible consolidation of partsand supply depots, base closures, doing away with cumbersomeregulations and streamlining accounting and finance systems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information Resources ManagementReorganizationUnited States. Department of DefenseEmployee RelationsPurchasing Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andO;Person:    Cheney, Dick (management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>